OL,7,F"When Colin first died we really just
OL,8,Fthought it was an unfortunate
OL,9,Faccident. (But) he was used. He was a
OL,10,Fguinea pig.
OL,12,F"To be able to go up (to Colin's
OL,13,Fgrave), hopefully Tuesday, and say
OL,14,F'you've done it darling, you have done
OL,15,Fit', it's going to be immense. It's
OL,16,Fgoing to be tearful, but it's going to
OL,17,Fbe beautiful."
OL,19,FBut for dad Colin, he doesn't feel an
OL,20,Fapology is appropriate.
